                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.731/127: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-15T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 15, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 15—3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1988. Your 909, September 13, 8 p.m. Western Union general manager in France
                    misunderstood present status of problem. The <pb facs="0550" n="542"
                        xml:id="pg_542"/> Supreme Army Council is still studying problem. Final
                    decision is expected soon, but until decision is taken the Commission de
                    Controle Télégraphique Internationale transmits promptly all transit telegrams
                    either in code or in plain language. All telegrams from and to France are
                    examined. Delay in transmission is insignificant for telegrams in any of eight
                    codes mentioned in my 1786. Delay is much greater and non-delivery possible for
                    those in non-usual codes. All rulings apply both to cable and radiotelegraph
                    companies. Decision of Supreme Army Council will be forwarded as soon as
                    received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
